The '''crust''' of a piece of [[bread]] is the edge where it is harder and darker.
Crust can also mean: *[[Crust (geology)]] - the outer solid layer of a planet such as the Earth but other planets also. *On Earth the crust can be divided into: **[[continental crust]] on which the land of the planet Earth sits **[[oceanic crust]] which forms most of the ocean floor
